  "texts": [
    "Through this meticulous process, the system adeptly balances the need for external data with the imperative to maintain swift and seamless text generation, exemplifying a sophisticated implementation of real-time data integration within a large language model framework.Below is a simplified Python code snippet illustrating the process of handling queries with the Google Query API: import requests def query_google_api(query): url = \"https://www.googleapis.com/customsearch/v1\" params = { \"key\": \"API_KEY\", \"cx\": \"CUSTOM_SEARCH_ENGINE_ID\", \"q\": query, } response = requests.get(url, params=params) return response.",
    "This code demonstrates the essential steps in querying the Google API based on the context of the input and integrating the response into the text generation process.",
    "The functions needs external info, construct query, parse response, and generate text are placeholders for the respective logic implementations within the integrated system.",
    "ResultsThis section delineates the empirical findings regarding the \"Llama 2 7b\" model's performance post-augmentation with the Google Search API.",
    "Accuracy ImprovementsThe augmentation of \"Llama 2 7b\" with the Google Search API has led to significant accuracy improvements, particularly observable across tasks specifically designed to assess linguistic comprehension, reasoning, and sentiment analysis capabilities."
